HEADWORD: Dreamer
<hw>Dream"er</hw> <pr>(dr⟦emac⟧m"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who dreams.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A visionary; one lost in wild imaginations or vain
schemes of some anticipated good; <as>as, a political
<ex>dreamer</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dreamful</ent>⟦br⟧
